# Deployment Options for Hostinger (Beyond FTP)

You have several options to deploy your eco-landing sites to Hostinger hosting. Here are all the available methods:

## üîÑ **Option 1: FTP Deployment (Current Setup)**
**‚úÖ Pros:** Works with all Hostinger plans, reliable, automatic
**‚ùå Cons:** Requires FTP credentials

This is what we've set up with GitHub Actions using `SamKirkland/FTP-Deploy-Action`.

---

## üêô **Option 2: Git Integration (Recommended Alternative)**

### GitHub Integration in Hostinger
Many Hostinger plans support direct Git deployment:

1. **Log into Hostinger Control Panel**
2. Look for **"Git"** or **"Version Control"** section
3. **Connect your GitHub repository**
4. **Set auto-deployment** on push to main branch

**‚úÖ Pros:** No FTP needed, direct from GitHub, very secure
**‚ùå Cons:** Not available on all Hostinger plans

### Setup Steps:
```bash
# In Hostinger Control Panel
1. Go to Git/Version Control
2. Add Repository: https://github.com/nishidshajib/eco-landing
3. Set Branch: main
4. Set Deploy Path: /public_html/ or /domains/yoursite.com/public_html/
5. Enable Auto-Deploy on Push
```

---

## üåê **Option 3: Hostinger Website Builder Integration**

### If you're using Hostinger's Website Builder:
1. **Export your Hugo sites** to static HTML
2. **Upload via Hostinger's drag-and-drop interface**
3. **Set up webhooks** to trigger rebuilds

**‚úÖ Pros:** No technical setup, visual interface
**‚ùå Cons:** Manual process, less automation

